      "type": "Potential Long Overflow",
      "description": "In the `addAndCheck` method, there's a potential long overflow when adding two `long` values. The method checks for overflow and throws an `ArithmeticException`, but it's still a potential issue if the addition results in a value that exceeds the range of `long`.",
      "line": 44
    },
    {
      "type": "Unused Private Constructor",
      "description": "The `MathUtils` class has a private constructor, which is unnecessary as the class is public and the constructor is not called anywhere in the code.",
      "line": 25
    },
    {
      "type": "Unused Final Fields",
      "description": "The constants `NB`, `NS`, `PB`, `PS`, `ZB`, and `ZS` are declared as `final` but are never used in the code. They could be removed to reduce the size of the class.",
      "line": 28
    },
    {
      "type": "Potential NPE in Arrays",
      "description": "The `FACTORIALS` array is initialized with a size of 24, but the largest value of `n` for which all coefficients are less than `Long.MAX_VALUE` is 66. If the method is used with `n > 23`, it may throw a `NullPointerException` when trying to access the array at an index greater than 23.",
      "line": 30
    }
  ]
